HEADWORD: Mackinaw boat
<hw>Mack"i*naw boat</hw></mhw>. <def>A
flat-bottomed boat with a pointed prow and square stern, using oars or
sails or both, used esp. on the upper Great Lakes and their
tributaries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

